               <msContents>
                  <summary/>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                        <locus from="1r" to="32r">Fols 1r–32r</locus>
                     <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1979Mashaf">Maṣḥafa ziq</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez" otherLangs="am"/>
                    <notatedMusic>
                        <desc>The text contains musical notation
                           written above the lines.</desc>
                     </notatedMusic>
                     <note>
                       The text is an unfinished compilation of short excerpts from the
                       <hi rendition="simple:italic">Maṣḥafa ziq za-Gʷandar</hi>,
                        beginning with chants <hi rendition="simple:italic">Za-baʿatā salām</hi>
                       (cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/F3W9GTEG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Ziq1970"/><title level="m">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;የዚቅ፡ መጽሐፈ። (&lt;/hi&gt;Ya-ziq maṣḥaf&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, ‘Book of the ziq')&lt;/hi&gt;</title><author><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʿĀmda Ṣəyon Tasammā</t:name></author><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Tǝnśāʾe za-gubāʾe māttamiyā bet</publisher><date>1970</date><citedRange unit="page">8a</citedRange></bibl>)
                        and <hi rendition="simple:italic">Salām</hi> for
                   <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5741Johnthe">John the Baptist</persName>
                   (cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/F3W9GTEG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Ziq1970"/><title level="m">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;የዚቅ፡ መጽሐፈ። (&lt;/hi&gt;Ya-ziq maṣḥaf&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, ‘Book of the ziq')&lt;/hi&gt;</title><author><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʿĀmda Ṣəyon Tasammā</t:name></author><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Tǝnśāʾe za-gubāʾe māttamiyā bet</publisher><date>1970</date><citedRange unit="page">10b</citedRange></bibl>).
                        The text ends with short chants for the feasts of
                        John the Baptist, <hi rendition="simple:italic">Ṣǝge</hi>, <hi rendition="simple:italic">Qʷǝsqʷām</hi>,
                        and St George of Lydda.
                           The last month indication is for Ḫǝdār (with no text).
                        Spaces for rubricated dates and section incipits have
                          been left empty in the second half of the manuscript.
                     </note>

                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        <locus target="#3r">Fol. 3r</locus>
                        <hi rend="rubric">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈ<supplied reason="lost" resp="DR">ስ፡ ቅ</supplied>ዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡ ን<supplied resp="DR" reason="lost">ቀ</supplied>ድም፡
